The paper deals with graph spanners, which are a fundamental topic in computer science and graph theory. The paper's main result is for the Lowest Degree 2-Spanner (LD2S) problem, which is a problem in graph theory and falls under the category of graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.DM) to design the algorithm. Additionally, the paper involves linear programming (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.GT) to establish a formal connection between LD2S and a variant of the Densest k-Subgraph (DkS) problem.
